at0005.1.description: Name of the laboratory investigation performed on the specimen.
at0005.1.comment: A test result may be for a single analyte, or a group of items, including panel tests. May be coded terminologies for example, LOINC or SNOMED CT. Examples include 'Glucose', 'Urea and Electrolytes', 'Swab', “Cortisol (am)” , "Potassium in perspiration" or "Liver Biopsy". The name may sometimes include specimen type and patient state, for example "Fasting blood glucose" or include other information, as "Potassium (PNA blood gas)".

at0000.1.description: The result of a laboratory test for a single analyte value.
at0000.1.comment: For example: 'Sodium', 'White cell count', 'T3'. Commonly coded with an external terminology,

at0024.1.description: Actual value of the analyte result. The value of this element is normally supplied in a specialisation, in a template or at run-time to reflect the actual analyte.
at0024.1.comment: e.g. 'Serum sodium', 'Haemoglobin'. Normally coded terminologies will be used for example, LOINC, NPU or SNOMED CT, or local lab terminologies.
